383
00:22:40,599 --> 00:22:41,629
It's just for PR.

384
00:22:43,219 --> 00:22:44,059
PR?

385
00:22:44,989 --> 00:22:49,449
The recent survey shows
that MSC's weak point is our credibility.

386
00:22:49,549 --> 00:22:51,549
We have to do something to change that

387
00:22:51,959 --> 00:22:53,229
and it reminds me of you.

388
00:22:53,549 --> 00:22:56,219
If we promote that we've hired
a reporter who can't lie,

389
00:22:56,319 --> 00:22:58,099
then it may help boost our credibility.

390
00:23:04,779 --> 00:23:06,279
Are you saying
that I'm not being chosen...

391
00:23:08,499 --> 00:23:10,969
as a reporter but as a promotional doll?

392
00:23:11,939 --> 00:23:12,779
Yeah.

393
00:23:13,439 --> 00:23:15,855
Think of it as a three month internship,
rather than a permanent.

394
00:23:16,309 --> 00:23:17,884
But if you do a good job,

395
00:23:17,975 --> 00:23:19,442
we may consider you
for a full time position.

396
00:23:21,209 --> 00:23:22,209
I'm not interested.

397
00:23:23,629 --> 00:23:25,629
Considering your current situation...

398
00:23:26,299 --> 00:23:28,829
I don't think you're in any position
to refuse my offer.

399
00:23:29,919 --> 00:23:33,009
Does honor or pride have any importance
in this matter?

400
00:23:33,419 --> 00:23:34,259
Yes.

401
00:23:34,799 --> 00:23:36,889
Those things do matter to me.

402
00:23:36,980 --> 00:23:38,379
In your current situation...

403
00:23:38,999 --> 00:23:42,689
I doubt you'd find any other way to become
a reporter while caring for such things.

404
00:23:47,969 --> 00:23:49,409
That's what decision making is.

405
00:23:50,079 --> 00:23:52,709
In order to gain something,
you have to throw something else away.

406
00:23:53,129 --> 00:23:54,009
Then...

407
00:23:54,979 --> 00:23:57,201
what did you throw away
when you chose to become a reporter?

408
00:23:59,959 --> 00:24:00,799
You.

409
00:24:04,969 --> 00:24:05,969
Did you...

410
00:24:07,449 --> 00:24:08,939
ever regret it?

411
00:24:10,929 --> 00:24:11,969
I did regret it.

412
00:24:19,809 --> 00:24:22,999
But seeing how you're dwelling
on that fact,

413
00:24:23,089 --> 00:24:24,749
I wonder if my regrets were in vain.

414
00:24:27,869 --> 00:24:30,690
If you decide to come, then get rid
of that hiccup before coming.

415
00:24:58,019 --> 00:24:58,899
Let's go.

416
00:25:02,179 --> 00:25:04,149
Sung Cha-ok - Local News Department Head

417
00:25:07,599 --> 00:25:09,609
I thought she came
because it's my birthday.

418
00:25:30,339 --> 00:25:31,229
So...

419
00:25:31,689 --> 00:25:33,869
do you think she'll work for MSC?

420
00:25:34,769 --> 00:25:36,809
Yes, I think so.

421
00:25:41,159 --> 00:25:42,829
Doesn’t she have any pride?

422
00:25:43,249 --> 00:25:46,319
She still wants to become a reporter
even after the way her mom treated her?

423
00:25:46,409 --> 00:25:47,679
That's what I'm saying.

424
00:25:49,839 --> 00:25:50,739
I thought...

425
00:25:51,559 --> 00:25:54,309
all mothers in this world
were as wonderful as my mom.

426
00:25:54,419 --> 00:25:55,459
I guess that's not it.

427
00:25:56,159 --> 00:25:57,639
Did you just figure that out?

428
00:25:59,889 --> 00:26:01,049
I'm curious about, Mother.

429
00:26:01,139 --> 00:26:02,019
About what?

430
00:26:02,539 --> 00:26:03,809
What's so important

431
00:26:03,899 --> 00:26:06,389
about being a reporter that she's willing
to endure that kind of treatment?

432
00:26:06,979 --> 00:26:08,979
