530
00:33:18,204 --> 00:33:21,624
An angel who remembered my birthday,
when the rest of my family didn't.

531
00:33:30,734 --> 00:33:31,574
So good!

532
00:33:35,884 --> 00:33:37,244
That's not allowed to happen.

533
00:33:37,934 --> 00:33:38,934
We're family.

534
00:33:58,064 --> 00:33:59,064
I can do this.

535
00:34:00,204 --> 00:34:01,204
I can do this.

536
00:34:09,694 --> 00:34:10,694
Have you decided?

537
00:34:11,934 --> 00:34:12,774
Yes.

538
00:34:18,374 --> 00:34:19,537
Seonbae.

539
00:34:19,914 --> 00:34:21,413
Are you back from the police station?

540
00:34:21,504 --> 00:34:22,344
Yeah.

541
00:34:24,734 --> 00:34:25,794
Have you heard the news?

542
00:34:25,974 --> 00:34:27,724
The new hire position that just opened up

543
00:34:28,074 --> 00:34:29,954
will be filled by someone
with connections.

544
00:34:37,394 --> 00:34:39,784
Yes, I heard one is through Ms Song

545
00:34:40,004 --> 00:34:42,534
and the other is through Mr Yeon.

546
00:34:42,764 --> 00:34:44,194
Do they think it's the air force?

547
00:34:44,284 --> 00:34:45,894
Who gets parachuted in like that?

548
00:34:46,764 --> 00:34:47,954
Don't try to stop me.

549
00:34:48,144 --> 00:34:49,874
I'm not going to sit back and accept this.

550
00:34:50,154 --> 00:34:52,024
I'll complain about it
to the internal board.

551
00:34:52,684 --> 00:34:55,434
I'm going to show them
what insubordination truly means.

552
00:34:55,974 --> 00:34:58,744
Even they get in through connection,
they do have good qualification.

553
00:34:58,834 --> 00:35:00,874
Both of them made it
to the final round at YGN.

554
00:35:01,534 --> 00:35:03,454
-And nice visuals, too.
-How do visuals matter...

555
00:35:03,544 --> 00:35:04,664
for reporters?

556
00:35:05,114 --> 00:35:07,184
Good looks don't write the news
and good looks

557
00:35:07,284 --> 00:35:08,666
don't get you exclusive news either.

558
00:35:11,854 --> 00:35:13,224
Hello.

559
00:35:13,314 --> 00:35:14,444
-Are you heading up?
-No.

560
00:35:14,534 --> 00:35:15,684
-Excuse me.
-Excuse me.

561
00:35:15,774 --> 00:35:16,694
Excuse me.

562
00:35:18,274 --> 00:35:19,844
-What are you doing...?
-You came.

563
00:35:20,924 --> 00:35:22,114
-Hello.
-Hello.

564
00:35:23,844 --> 00:35:24,864
Say hello.

565
00:35:24,974 --> 00:35:27,013
This is Kim Gong-joo,
Captain in charge of the police station.

566
00:35:27,434 --> 00:35:29,974
And that's Reporter Lee Il-joo,
in charge of Han River district.

567
00:35:30,734 --> 00:35:32,874
These are our new intern reporters.

568
00:35:33,134 --> 00:35:34,334
Choi In-ha and Seo Bum-Jo.

569
00:35:35,744 --> 00:35:36,834
Nice to meet you.

570
00:35:37,324 --> 00:35:39,084
Welcome to MSC.

571
00:35:40,774 --> 00:35:44,114
One thing that we lacked in comparison
to YGN is our reporters' good looks.

572
00:35:44,624 --> 00:35:47,164
But the situation seems turned in
with the arrival of these two.

573
00:35:48,614 --> 00:35:50,504
Choi In-ha, let's go down directly
to the studio.

574
00:35:50,594 --> 00:35:51,434
Yes, Ma'am.

575
00:35:57,405 --> 00:35:58,644
I need to talk to you for a bit.

576
00:35:58,814 --> 00:35:59,654
Yes, Sir.

577
00:36:01,944 --> 00:36:04,094
Is your mother doing well?

578
00:36:06,534 --> 00:36:07,984
I thought you were going
to insubordinate?

579
00:36:08,074 --> 00:36:09,164
I just did.

580
00:36:09,784 --> 00:36:10,624
Pardon?

581
00:36:12,444 --> 00:36:14,874
I only mentioned their looks,
not their skills at all.

582
00:36:15,404 --> 00:36:17,334
Unless they're stupid, they'll realize

583
00:36:17,424 --> 00:36:19,644
that was a form of disrespect
to their skills.

584
00:36:20,344 --> 00:36:22,874
I bet Mr Yeon and Ms Song
both took note of it.

585
00:36:26,474 --> 00:36:28,184
Whatever!

586
00:36:36,504 --> 00:36:37,824
This is a draft of the PR shoot.

587
00:36:38,084 --> 00:36:39,724
Let me know if you don't understand.

588
00:36:39,914 --> 00:36:40,754
Yes.

589
00:36:41,354 --> 00:36:43,444
When will these start airing?

590
00:36:44,734 --> 00:36:46,254
Maybe some time within the week.

591
00:36:46,494 --> 00:36:47,664
-Why do you ask?
-Nothing.

592
00:36:47,754 --> 00:36:48,594
Just asking.

593
00:36:50,184 --> 00:36:52,334
Did you not tell your father
about you coming here?

594
00:36:53,904 --> 00:36:55,394
No, not yet.

595
00:36:56,124 --> 00:36:57,904
I'm going to tell him soon.

596
00:36:58,994 --> 00:37:00,384
Are those the only shoes you have?

597
00:37:00,554 --> 00:37:01,394
Excuse me?

598
00:37:03,234 --> 00:37:04,074
Yes.

599
00:37:10,814 --> 00:37:11,954
Wear those for now.

600
00:37:12,184 --> 00:37:13,344
Yours are too shabby.

601
00:37:15,364 --> 00:37:17,254
This is Choi In-ha, from MSC News.

602
00:37:17,344 --> 00:37:18,224
Ms In-ha.

603
00:37:18,364 --> 00:37:19,744
Let's give it a try one more time.

604
00:37:19,904 --> 00:37:21,514
As you have just seen,

605
00:37:21,604 --> 00:37:23,514
I'm a Pinocchio,
and thus, cannot tell a lie.

606
00:37:23,604 --> 00:37:25,794
And I'm the first Pinocchio reporter
in Korea.

607
00:37:25,884 --> 00:37:28,044
-There are two promises...
-Let's go one more time.

608
00:37:31,364 --> 00:37:32,524
Ready, Cue!

609
00:37:32,704 --> 00:37:34,314
I'm a Pinocchio, and thus, cannot lie.

610
00:37:34,404 --> 00:37:36,444
And I'm the first Pinocchio
reporter in Korea.

611
00:37:36,534 --> 00:37:38,414
This is Choi In-ha, from MSC News.

612
00:37:40,324 --> 00:37:44,024
Your core as a trainee reporter
is the National Forensics Lab.

613
00:37:44,204 --> 00:37:46,334
Here, a single strand of hair
or fingerprint found

614
00:37:46,514 --> 00:37:48,314
at a crime scene,
determines a person's life.

615
00:37:48,404 --> 00:37:49,894
The same applies to over a news case.

616
00:37:50,154 --> 00:37:52,694
You must think of everything found
at a crime scene as evidence

617
00:37:52,784 --> 00:37:54,414
and be able to bet your life on it.

618
00:37:55,094 --> 00:37:56,754
The power of science that reveals truth.

619
00:37:57,004 --> 00:37:58,214
You must know that power

620
00:37:58,584 --> 00:38:00,584
in order for you to decode your own truth.

621
00:38:00,964 --> 00:38:01,994
And also...

622
00:38:02,914 --> 00:38:06,404
you will be able to attend
the human autopsy.

623
00:38:06,494 --> 00:38:08,204
The highlight of this whole tour.

624
00:38:08,374 --> 00:38:09,614
You can look forward to it.

625
00:38:12,764 --> 00:38:15,284
This is the corpse of a 41-year-old male.

626
00:38:16,224 --> 00:38:18,464
Even though it may appear
that he was burned to death,

627
00:38:19,064 --> 00:38:22,134
there's no indication
of any smoke inhalation in the lungs.

628
00:38:22,434 --> 00:38:24,414
It means, he's already dead
before his body burned.

629
00:38:24,504 --> 00:38:27,734
From the condition of the esophagus
and the gastro-intestines,

630
00:38:27,824 --> 00:38:29,859
it seems that poisoning
was the real cause of death.

631
00:38:30,384 --> 00:38:31,654
Are you okay?

632
00:38:32,144 --> 00:38:33,834
I have to get through this
even if I'm not.

633
00:38:34,224 --> 00:38:35,724
I can't get targeted again.

634
00:38:36,254 --> 00:38:39,242
Should we have ox blood soup,
or intestine soup for lunch?

635
00:38:39,333 --> 00:38:40,783
Intestine soup sounds good.

636
00:38:41,544 --> 00:38:42,644
What the...

637
00:38:43,334 --> 00:38:45,334
What the... What...

638
00:38:46,054 --> 00:38:46,894
Yu-Rae!

639
00:38:47,784 --> 00:38:48,784
Yu-Rae.

640
00:38:51,004 --> 00:38:53,004
Don’t look back!

641
00:39:06,014 --> 00:39:07,423
Have you told your father?

642
00:39:12,644 --> 00:39:13,654
I'm home.

643
00:39:14,354 --> 00:39:15,274
Come, sit down.

644
00:39:15,524 --> 00:39:16,444
Let's have dinner.

645
00:39:16,664 --> 00:39:17,504
Okay.

646
00:39:18,044 --> 00:39:20,214
Why do you wear a suit when you work
at a convenience store?

647
00:39:20,304 --> 00:39:22,004
Did they hire you as a full-time employee?

648
00:39:22,144 --> 00:39:24,344
Stop irritating her. That’s enough.

649
00:39:25,184 --> 00:39:26,964
Dad, Grandfather.

650
00:39:27,264 --> 00:39:29,264
-The truth is...
-I'm home.

651
00:39:29,464 --> 00:39:31,124
Welcome home, Dal-Po.

652
00:39:31,384 --> 00:39:33,084
Let's all sit down to dinner.

653
00:39:34,174 --> 00:39:35,014
Sure.

654
00:39:38,304 --> 00:39:39,614
What is this?

655
00:39:39,704 --> 00:39:41,994
I made your favorite tripe soup.

656
00:39:43,284 --> 00:39:45,284
I put lots of tripe and intestines,

657
00:39:45,434 --> 00:39:46,611
so it has a very deep flavor.

658
00:39:48,734 --> 00:39:49,574
What's wrong?

659
00:39:50,414 --> 00:39:51,483
Uncle, what's wrong?

660
00:39:53,294 --> 00:39:54,484
It's nothing.

661
00:39:56,124 --> 00:39:57,204
Oh, my.

662
00:39:58,314 --> 00:39:59,154
Here.

663
00:40:06,824 --> 00:40:07,824
Dal-Po.

664
00:40:09,334 --> 00:40:10,274
Dal-Po.

665
00:40:10,474 --> 00:40:11,684
-What's wrong with him?
-Oh, my.

666
00:40:11,774 --> 00:40:13,194
Does man get morning sickness, too?

667
00:40:26,934 --> 00:40:28,344
Don't get any wrong ideas!

668
00:40:36,734 --> 00:40:37,754
It's cold out.

669
00:40:38,974 --> 00:40:39,814
Dal-Po.

670
00:40:44,254 --> 00:40:45,354
How do you feel?

671
00:40:46,700 --> 00:40:48,000
Here, I've bought medicine.

672
00:40:50,234 --> 00:40:51,084
I'm fine.

673
00:40:51,174 --> 00:40:52,904
You're making yourself sick
from exhaustion.

674
00:40:53,234 --> 00:40:54,874
The job is stressful, isn't it?

675
00:40:55,814 --> 00:40:56,654
No.

676
00:40:56,844 --> 00:40:58,114
It's okay. I like it.

677
00:41:00,124 --> 00:41:02,574
Keeping things bottled
in will make you sick.

678
00:41:03,034 --> 00:41:04,614
You can't do anything if you get sick.

679
00:41:04,914 --> 00:41:07,284
You have to tell people if you're ill

680
00:41:07,514 --> 00:41:08,844
in order to treat the illness.

681
00:41:09,084 --> 00:41:11,104
And let others know
when you're struggling,

682
00:41:11,254 --> 00:41:13,244
so that people can help you.

683
00:41:13,864 --> 00:41:14,804
Do you understand?

684
00:41:15,434 --> 00:41:16,274
Yes.

685
00:41:16,454 --> 00:41:17,374
I know.

686
00:41:17,614 --> 00:41:19,034
I'll let you know if I'm struggling.

687
00:41:19,584 --> 00:41:20,424
Alright.

688
00:41:20,574 --> 00:41:22,334
-Just keep that in mind.
-Hyungnim.

689
00:41:23,964 --> 00:41:24,824
Eat this.

690
00:41:25,284 --> 00:41:26,774
Take one dose 30 minutes after meal.

691
00:41:27,294 --> 00:41:28,934
I'm the only one who care of you, right?

692
00:41:29,214 --> 00:41:30,674
Geez.

693
00:41:31,964 --> 00:41:33,934
You're several steps too late.

694
00:41:34,694 --> 00:41:36,264
I already got him some medicine.

695
00:41:40,424 --> 00:41:41,264
Thanks.

696
00:42:23,454 --> 00:42:24,964
Dad still not out yet?

697
00:42:32,244 --> 00:42:33,894
Yeah, he's taking his time.

698
00:42:37,474 --> 00:42:38,464
I'm late.

699
00:42:38,654 --> 00:42:40,654
I'll wash up first.

700
00:42:41,704 --> 00:42:42,984
Where do you think you're going?

701
00:42:43,144 --> 00:42:44,374
I'm late, too.

702
00:42:44,804 --> 00:42:47,354
But I won't take long.

703
00:42:50,084 --> 00:42:51,272
I said, I'm late, too.

704
00:42:53,424 --> 00:42:54,654
Move your hand.

705
00:42:55,054 --> 00:42:55,994
No!

706
00:43:01,024 --> 00:43:03,334
It will be really hard for you
if you go in right now.

707
00:43:09,224 --> 00:43:10,434
-You go first
-No!

708
00:43:10,764 --> 00:43:11,614
No!

709
00:43:11,864 --> 00:43:13,274
No, you go in first.

710
00:43:13,364 --> 00:43:14,284
Seriously!

711
00:43:21,174 --> 00:43:23,884
You said you're running late,
so I'm letting you go first.

712
00:43:23,974 --> 00:43:27,034
Dad! What did you eat last night?

713
00:43:27,284 --> 00:43:29,435
This smells like trash!

714
00:43:38,394 --> 00:43:40,614
These are papers from a trash can
of Homicide department.

715
00:43:40,704 --> 00:43:41,864
Put these back together

716
00:43:42,264 --> 00:43:44,064
and see if you find something newsworthy.

717
00:43:44,294 --> 00:43:45,314
Understood?

718
00:43:45,604 --> 00:43:46,624
-Excuse me?
-Excuse me?

719
00:43:47,774 --> 00:43:50,314
It's almost time to go home.
When are we ever going to...

720
00:43:51,884 --> 00:43:53,474
We can get it done.

721
00:43:53,564 --> 00:43:55,934
No one goes home until this is finished.

722
00:43:57,624 --> 00:43:58,684
Understood?

723
00:43:59,124 --> 00:44:00,234
-Yes, Sir!
-Yes, Sir!

724
00:44:12,524 --> 00:44:15,864
I heard that Nitpicker Jang takes the
lowest scoring trainee under his wing.

725
00:44:16,304 --> 00:44:18,774
And I currently have
the lowest score, don't I?

726
00:44:19,904 --> 00:44:20,994
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

727
00:44:22,544 --> 00:44:24,654
That means I'll be with
Nitpicker Jang's, will I?

728
00:44:25,284 --> 00:44:26,124
Yeah.

729
00:44:26,494 --> 00:44:28,214
Are you crying?

730
00:44:28,364 --> 00:44:30,202
No, it's because I was yawning.

731
00:44:37,774 --> 00:44:38,614
Hey.

732
00:44:38,904 --> 00:44:40,524
You still haven't fixed the bumper?

733
00:44:41,044 --> 00:44:41,884
Why?

734
00:44:42,004 --> 00:44:43,764
Is the person responsible refused to pay?

735
00:44:43,854 --> 00:44:45,854
I'm just going to let him off the hook.

736
00:44:46,264 --> 00:44:47,304
It's just a slight dent.

737
00:44:47,434 --> 00:44:48,444
No.

738
00:44:48,534 --> 00:44:50,694
Don’t let it slide even for that person.

739
00:44:50,914 --> 00:44:52,294
If a person commits a wrongdoing,

740
00:44:52,384 --> 00:44:54,164
then they have to be responsible for it.

741
00:44:54,384 --> 00:44:57,244
Do you think he's going to be grateful
for you letting him off the hook?

742
00:44:57,334 --> 00:44:58,984
It'll just make him more irresponsible.

743
00:44:59,164 --> 00:45:00,014
Is that true?

744
00:45:00,104 --> 00:45:01,774
You have to make him pay for it.

745
00:45:01,864 --> 00:45:04,166
I told you that you can get 100 dollars
for the damage.

746
00:45:04,257 --> 00:45:05,097
Yes.

747
00:45:05,474 --> 00:45:06,394
I'll keep that in mind.

748
00:45:06,484 --> 00:45:07,484
Yeah, right.

749
00:45:08,744 --> 00:45:10,264
-Make sure to get the money.
-Okay.

750
00:45:33,844 --> 00:45:36,144
We could never ever finish this.

751
00:45:37,004 --> 00:45:37,844
I feel like...

752
00:45:38,334 --> 00:45:40,584
aged 10 years putting these back together.

753
00:45:41,254 --> 00:45:42,314
What are we going to do?

754
00:45:47,694 --> 00:45:48,534
Hello?

755
00:45:48,774 --> 00:45:49,614
Yes.

756
00:45:50,184 --> 00:45:52,304
The bumper? Of course, I remember.

757
00:45:52,744 --> 00:45:54,314
Of course, I'll
reimburse you for it.

758
00:45:54,674 --> 00:45:55,724
I'm glad you called.

759
00:45:56,264 --> 00:45:57,264
When would you...

760
00:45:59,564 --> 00:46:00,564
Right now?

761
00:46:02,294 --> 00:46:03,334
No, it's not that...

762
00:46:05,344 --> 00:46:06,624
Yes, I understand.

763
00:46:06,754 --> 00:46:07,864
I'll be right there.

764
00:46:08,594 --> 00:46:10,474
Hey, where do you think you're going?

765
00:46:10,794 --> 00:46:12,374
I have to step out real quick.

766
00:46:12,734 --> 00:46:14,024
Hey, are you out of your mind?

767
00:46:14,114 --> 00:46:16,134
Nitpicker Jang will kill you
if you get caught.

768
00:46:17,074 --> 00:46:18,814
Yes, where should I meet you?

769
00:46:18,994 --> 00:46:19,884
Hey, Dal-Po.

770
00:46:20,164 --> 00:46:21,914
How about somewhere around my house?

771
00:46:23,484 --> 00:46:24,874
Yes, my address is...

772
00:46:25,134 --> 00:46:25,974
Yes.

773
00:46:26,224 --> 00:46:27,314
Yes, I know where that is.

774
00:47:04,894 --> 00:47:06,744
Yes, I'm here.

775
00:47:06,934 --> 00:47:08,134
How far away are you?

776
00:47:08,964 --> 00:47:10,114
Please wait for a while.

777
00:47:10,204 --> 00:47:11,644
I'm almost there myself.

778
00:47:14,344 --> 00:47:15,184
Yes.

779
00:47:15,354 --> 00:47:16,324
I think I see the car.

780
00:47:32,054 --> 00:47:33,084
This isn't the truck.

781
00:47:33,244 --> 00:47:35,684
I'm a good friend of the truck owner.

782
00:47:36,004 --> 00:47:37,464
I was getting frustrated with him,

783
00:47:38,054 --> 00:47:39,104
so I called you myself.

784
00:47:39,334 --> 00:47:42,164
This is what his bumper looks like,

785
00:47:42,354 --> 00:47:43,794
yet he still won't get it fixed.

786
00:47:44,134 --> 00:47:44,984
Yes.

787
00:47:51,564 --> 00:47:53,314
He's just a big softie,

788
00:47:53,644 --> 00:47:55,224
so he'd never ask for compensation.

789
00:47:55,474 --> 00:47:56,774
But it frustrates me,

790
00:47:56,864 --> 00:47:59,143
so instead, I'm asking in his place.

791
00:47:59,294 --> 00:48:00,301
That's why I'm here.

792
00:48:00,664 --> 00:48:03,154
I just felt business is business.

793
00:48:03,734 --> 00:48:05,174
Yes, I'm glad you did.

794
00:48:11,304 --> 00:48:13,474
-Mr Moon Duk-soo?
-Yes.

795
00:48:16,084 --> 00:48:18,924
Are you the one who called
about my missing wallet?

796
00:48:19,244 --> 00:48:21,684
Yes, but I don't have the wallet
on me right now.

797
00:48:22,284 --> 00:48:24,444
I came straight here after work,
so it's still at home.

798
00:48:25,634 --> 00:48:26,904
Okay.

799
00:48:27,534 --> 00:48:30,004
My house is around the corner.
Why don't you come with me?

800
00:48:31,604 --> 00:48:32,604
Well... sure.

801
00:48:41,304 --> 00:48:42,874
I didn't know anyone lived around here.

802
00:48:43,604 --> 00:48:45,569
Everything looks demolished.

803
00:48:46,194 --> 00:48:47,894
My house is just around that corner.

804
00:48:51,074 --> 00:48:52,984
Sorry, but may I borrow your cellphone?

805
00:48:53,904 --> 00:48:55,254
Mine just ran out of battery.

806
00:48:58,834 --> 00:49:00,464
-Make it short.
-Thank you.

807
00:49:00,984 --> 00:49:02,074
We can just keep walking.

808
00:49:06,184 --> 00:49:07,184
It's cold.

809
00:49:54,114 --> 00:49:55,864
Was I not clear about no one going home

810
00:49:55,954 --> 00:49:57,884
until you put all the papers
back together?

811
00:49:58,024 --> 00:49:58,864
Yes, you were.

812
00:49:59,184 --> 00:50:00,024
I'm sorry.

813
00:50:00,454 --> 00:50:02,644
Everyone, pack your belongings
and go home.

814
00:50:04,324 --> 00:50:05,254
Get up!

815
00:50:05,364 --> 00:50:06,224
That startled me.

816
00:50:07,664 --> 00:50:08,524
And also!

817
00:50:10,054 --> 00:50:13,234
Choi Dal-Po will finish putting the rest
of these together before going home.

818
00:50:13,994 --> 00:50:15,174
Yes, I understand.

819
00:50:21,604 --> 00:50:22,944
That’s too bad for Choi Dal-Po.

820
00:50:23,034 --> 00:50:25,374
I think he's definitely been targeted
by Nitpicker Jang.

821
00:50:26,234 --> 00:50:29,224
I feel bad for Choi Dal-Po,
but thanks to him

822
00:50:29,524 --> 00:50:31,180
we've escaped being assigned
under Nitpicker Jang.

823
00:50:31,764 --> 00:50:33,064
I feel really bad for Dal-Po.

824
00:50:37,734 --> 00:50:39,664
Hey, are you smiling right now?

825
00:50:42,064 --> 00:50:43,584
-No.
-No, I think you were.

826
00:50:43,884 --> 00:50:45,014
No, I didn't.

827
00:50:45,364 --> 00:50:47,574
Dal-Po goes to Han River district...

828
00:50:47,934 --> 00:50:49,017
God! I must've lost my mind.

829
00:50:49,474 --> 00:50:52,624
It's just that I feel bad
about Dal-Po falling

830
00:50:53,544 --> 00:50:55,114
under Nitpicker's jurisdiction.

831
00:51:05,174 --> 00:51:06,714
Wow, your connection is the Director?

832
00:51:06,804 --> 00:51:07,824
Cool!

833
00:51:07,914 --> 00:51:09,784
Just lower your speech
since we're coworkers now.

834
00:51:09,874 --> 00:51:10,714
Should I?

835
00:51:10,834 --> 00:51:13,934
But the name, Bum-Jo, sounds familiar.
Where have I heard that name before?

836
00:51:14,024 --> 00:51:16,634
It's the name of a department store.
'Bum-Jo Department Store'.

837
00:51:17,294 --> 00:51:18,474
The store was named after me.

838
00:51:19,224 --> 00:51:20,164
Is that right?

839
00:51:20,544 --> 00:51:22,634
There's a university
that's been named after me, too.

840
00:51:23,044 --> 00:51:24,124
I'm being serious.

841
00:51:24,704 --> 00:51:25,954
Hey, want this?

842
00:51:26,954 --> 00:51:28,354
This is what I like the most.

843
00:51:29,394 --> 00:51:31,614
But doesn't it seem like
we see each other quite often?

844
00:51:32,064 --> 00:51:33,174
Is it just coincidence?

845
00:51:33,264 --> 00:51:34,894
How can it be just coincidence?

846
00:51:35,824 --> 00:51:36,834
The truth is...

847
00:51:37,894 --> 00:51:41,334
The inability to lie can be a weakness
as a reporter.

848
00:51:41,424 --> 00:51:42,264
No.

849
00:51:42,554 --> 00:51:44,234
I see it as a positive merit.

850
00:51:44,354 --> 00:51:46,354
Reporters are supposed to tell the truth.

851
00:51:46,574 --> 00:51:49,624
News reports being created and told
by a reporter who can't lie

852
00:51:50,004 --> 00:51:51,824
will lend more credibility to the viewers.

853
00:51:52,224 --> 00:51:53,064
No.

854
00:51:53,154 --> 00:51:54,144
I can guarantee it.

855
00:51:54,434 --> 00:51:57,724
As you have just seen,
I'm a Pinocchio, and thus, cannot lie.

856
00:51:58,074 --> 00:52:00,824
And I'm also the first Pinocchio reporter
in this country.

857
00:52:00,924 --> 00:52:05,384
As your new MSC news reporter,
I can promise you two things.

858
00:52:06,424 --> 00:52:07,264
First.

859
00:52:07,364 --> 00:52:09,194
I will only relay the truth.

860
00:52:09,554 --> 00:52:10,394
Second.

861
00:52:10,504 --> 00:52:13,614
I promise to keep my first promise.

862
00:52:15,194 --> 00:52:17,274
I'm Choi In-ha from MSC News.

863
00:52:18,004 --> 00:52:19,204
I'm Choi In-ha...

864
00:52:20,184 --> 00:52:21,574
from MSC News.

865
00:52:25,954 --> 00:52:27,874
Who cares whether
it was coincidence or not?

866
00:52:29,194 --> 00:52:30,874
All that matters
is that we've finally met.

867
00:52:41,334 --> 00:52:42,294
Hello, Sir.

868
00:52:42,574 --> 00:52:43,574
Carry on.

869
00:52:46,724 --> 00:52:49,854
It'll be no joke once Jang Hyun-gyu
makes up his mind to pick on someone.

870
00:52:50,354 --> 00:52:51,774
Don't you find this to be a vicious?

871
00:52:52,004 --> 00:52:54,314
No, I don't think of it that way.

872
00:52:55,194 --> 00:52:56,714
If my memory serves me right,

873
00:52:57,014 --> 00:52:58,884
you're not someone
who'd be here doing this.

874
00:52:59,694 --> 00:53:02,784
And you're especially not someone
who'd listen to your senior

875
00:53:03,174 --> 00:53:04,374
just to become a reporter.

876
00:53:05,184 --> 00:53:06,294
I'm not sure what you're saying.

877
00:53:06,384 --> 00:53:07,714
Give me a straight answer.

878
00:53:07,874 --> 00:53:10,735
Because I remember every single word
that you said to me eight years ago.

879
00:53:12,064 --> 00:53:12,954
I'm not sure.

880
00:53:13,264 --> 00:53:15,084
I don't really remember.

881
00:53:15,404 --> 00:53:17,924
Why did you walk
into this sewage of a place?

882
00:53:18,434 --> 00:53:21,983
What made you become a reporter who
wields their mic and camera like weapons?

883
00:53:34,714 --> 00:53:35,844
Don't worry.

884
00:53:36,814 --> 00:53:38,094
It's just you and I in here.

885
00:53:38,354 --> 00:53:39,374
So...

886
00:53:39,534 --> 00:53:41,504
tell me the truth mano-a-mano.

887
00:53:42,474 --> 00:53:44,044
Because nothing you say in here...

888
00:53:44,534 --> 00:53:46,874
will be held against you,
and will be kept confidential.

889
00:53:48,374 --> 00:53:50,344
What do you want to be
a reporter all of a sudden?

890
00:53:50,854 --> 00:53:51,904
Did you suddenly...

891
00:53:52,674 --> 00:53:54,224
come to like reporter or something?

892
00:53:58,994 --> 00:54:00,054
Of course...

893
00:54:01,214 --> 00:54:02,244
that is not possible.

894
00:54:11,354 --> 00:54:13,354
I still find this place stifling

895
00:54:13,624 --> 00:54:15,294
and find reporters to be disgusting.

896
00:54:15,494 --> 00:54:16,334
Then...

897
00:54:17,084 --> 00:54:18,344
why are you here?

898
00:54:21,144 --> 00:54:22,194
It's because of my name.

899
00:54:23,234 --> 00:54:25,714
-Your name?
-I will do anything to get through

900
00:54:26,145 --> 00:54:28,145
this training period, and once I get

901
00:54:28,324 --> 00:54:30,674
my own mic in my hands,
I want to announce my real name.

902
00:54:33,484 --> 00:54:34,464
Your real name?

903
00:54:34,764 --> 00:54:36,944
Then, are you saying that...

904
00:54:37,564 --> 00:54:38,917
That your current name is a fake?

905
00:54:41,664 --> 00:54:42,504
Yes.

906
00:54:42,974 --> 00:54:44,444
What are you doing?

907
00:54:44,724 --> 00:54:46,404
Who the heck are you?

908
00:54:47,054 --> 00:54:49,124
You've got some impressive voice.

909
00:54:50,594 --> 00:54:51,964
But your efforts are useless.

910
00:54:52,594 --> 00:54:54,344
Like you said, this is a demolition site,

911
00:54:54,504 --> 00:54:55,664
so no one ever comes here.

912
00:54:56,694 --> 00:54:59,914
What wrong have I ever done
to you to deserve this?

913
00:55:00,624 --> 00:55:03,264
Answer me. Tell me who you are.

914
00:55:04,434 --> 00:55:06,084
What's your real name?

915
00:55:13,074 --> 00:55:15,034
I'm Firefighter Ki Ho-sang's son.

916
00:55:20,234 --> 00:55:21,264
Ki Ha-myung.

917
00:55:23,294 --> 00:55:24,134
What?

918
00:55:24,574 --> 00:55:26,374
Firefighter Ki Ho-sang?

919
00:55:28,054 --> 00:55:30,764
Do you remember...that name?

920
00:55:32,544 --> 00:55:34,664
The skeletal remains
that have recently been found.

921
00:55:35,764 --> 00:55:37,394
I'm that Firefighter Ki Ho-sang's son.

922
00:55:39,354 --> 00:55:40,194
What?

923
00:55:46,814 --> 00:55:47,654
What...

924
00:55:48,024 --> 00:55:49,769
What are you going to do to me?

925
00:55:51,904 --> 00:55:52,874
I want to...

926
00:55:54,144 --> 00:55:56,054
make you aware...

927
00:55:56,964 --> 00:55:58,374
of how my father passed away.

928
00:56:00,134 --> 00:56:03,534
You're that firefighter’s...son?

929
00:56:05,834 --> 00:56:06,674
Yes.

930
00:56:08,324 --> 00:56:09,494
Because of you people...

931
00:56:10,664 --> 00:56:12,374
I've lost both my mother and father,

932
00:56:12,724 --> 00:56:13,984
as well as my older brother.

933
00:56:16,644 --> 00:56:18,064
And I've also lost my own name.

934
00:56:19,864 --> 00:56:21,254
And very recently,

935
00:56:21,874 --> 00:56:25,174
I've also discovered how unjustly my
father passed away because of you people.

936
00:56:32,064 --> 00:56:35,364
I have so much to say
and just as many questions to ask.

937
00:56:35,924 --> 00:56:37,624
And there's a person
that I'd like to find.

938
00:56:41,904 --> 00:56:43,834
I thought long and hard...

939
00:56:44,234 --> 00:56:45,864
about who could accomplish
all those tasks.

940
00:56:51,334 --> 00:56:52,174
And...

941
00:56:54,244 --> 00:56:56,841
the answer I found left me astonished.

942
00:57:02,074 --> 00:57:03,804
You're going to die down in there.

943
00:57:06,674 --> 00:57:08,704
But no one will find out
about your death.

944
00:57:09,684 --> 00:57:11,894
They'll just believe
that you're hiding away somewhere.

945
00:57:12,654 --> 00:57:15,264
Don’t let me die in here!

946
00:57:15,444 --> 00:57:16,284
And...

947
00:57:19,314 --> 00:57:20,434
everyone in this world...

948
00:57:21,544 --> 00:57:24,574
will remember you as the devil
that killed your friends for their money.

949
00:57:27,444 --> 00:57:29,174
What do you mean by that?

950
00:57:29,854 --> 00:57:32,034
I've never killed anyone in my life!

951
00:57:37,194 --> 00:57:38,064
I know.

952
00:57:39,104 --> 00:57:40,654
But the world won't know that.

953
00:57:41,684 --> 00:57:43,344
Not even your own families.

954
00:57:46,574 --> 00:57:47,474
The world...

955
00:57:48,134 --> 00:57:50,914
will remember you as a murderer
and heinous criminal.

956
00:57:51,444 --> 00:57:54,704
Your family will live
the rest of their lives

957
00:57:54,794 --> 00:57:56,874
being taunted and insulted by others.

958
00:57:57,684 --> 00:58:00,554
They'll come to realize death isn't
the only way to experience pure hell.

959
00:58:00,644 --> 00:58:01,644
And was that answer...

960
00:58:02,994 --> 00:58:04,014
to become a reporter?

961
00:58:08,034 --> 00:58:09,064
Forgive me!

962
00:58:09,854 --> 00:58:11,684
I'm so sorry for my wrongdoing!

963
00:58:11,774 --> 00:58:12,914
Later on...

964
00:58:14,034 --> 00:58:16,974
even if you're lucky enough to have
your skeletal remains discovered...

965
00:58:17,394 --> 00:58:19,864
no one will have
even the slightest interest

966
00:58:19,954 --> 00:58:21,924
in finding out how wrongful
your death was!

967
00:58:22,224 --> 00:58:24,114
Just like my father!

968
00:58:33,924 --> 00:58:34,764
Yes.

969
00:58:36,954 --> 00:58:38,374
That's why I became a reporter.

970
00:58:39,094 --> 00:58:40,984
Because a reporter
can do all those things.

971
00:58:41,384 --> 00:58:43,384
So...

972
00:58:46,664 --> 00:58:49,624
Local News

973
00:58:51,834 --> 00:58:53,364
I'll try my best to learn the skills...

974
00:58:53,764 --> 00:58:54,604
Cap.

975
00:59:16,104 --> 00:59:17,054
Run immediately!

976
00:59:17,144 --> 00:59:18,964
I'm running, but I'll run faster!

977
00:59:19,054 --> 00:59:20,164
Yes, I understand.

978
00:59:20,374 --> 00:59:21,214
Uncle.

979
00:59:21,404 --> 00:59:23,764
-Why are you coming from there?
-He looked a lot like you.

980
00:59:23,854 --> 00:59:26,964
-Like me?
-You can use me as your helper.

981
00:59:27,104 --> 00:59:29,594
Ahn Chan-soo? We were never
close enough for this.

982
00:59:29,784 --> 00:59:32,544
Maybe they're settling together
in the police station.

983
00:59:32,634 --> 00:59:33,594
Those brats!

984
00:59:33,684 --> 00:59:35,124
Choi Dal-Po, you're my beginning.

985
00:59:35,219 --> 00:59:37,934
You're so nicely planted in here.
